About us


Science belongs to everyone


We’re a community of researchers, writers, educators, and curious minds working to close the gap between the lab and the living room. Founded in 2021, SciComm Collective runs a blog, a podcast, monthly in-person events, and training workshops — all centred on the belief that good science communication makes society smarter and more resilient.





&lt;div class="sc-label"&gt;What we believe&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="sc-values-grid"&gt;
  &lt;div class="sc-value-card"&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-icon"&gt;🔬&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-title"&gt;Accuracy over virality&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-desc"&gt;We never sacrifice scientific accuracy for a more exciting headline. When findings are uncertain, we say so.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="sc-value-card"&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-icon"&gt;🗣️&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-title"&gt;Dialogue, not broadcast&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-desc"&gt;Science communication works best as a conversation. We create spaces where the public shapes the agenda too.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="sc-value-card"&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-icon"&gt;🌍&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-title"&gt;Inclusion and access&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-desc"&gt;Most of our events and content are free. We work to platform voices underrepresented in science media.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="sc-value-card"&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-icon"&gt;✨&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-title"&gt;Craft matters&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="sc-value-desc"&gt;Good science communication is good writing, good storytelling, good listening. We take the craft seriously.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;





